-- 
Jaguar Land Rover to Build U.K. Engine Plant, Telegraph Reports

-- B y   A l e x   M o r a l e s
-- 
2011-09-18T10:34:04Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-18/jaguar-land-rover-to-build-u-k-engine-factory-telegraph-says.html
Jaguar Land Rover, the luxury car
unit of India’s  Tata Motors Ltd. (TTMT) , is set to announce that it’s
building a 400 million-pound ($631 million) engine plant in the
U.K., the Sunday Telegraph reported, citing an unidentified
person familiar with the plans.  The factory, which will create as many as 2,000 jobs, will
be built with some government funding in Wolverhampton, central
England, the Telegraph said. The plant may be announced tomorrow
by the company in conjunction with Business Secretary  Vince Cable , according to the newspaper.  Tata Motors spokesman Debasis Ray declined to comment when
contacted by telephone today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alex Morales in London at 
